dc:title: 96-11-080AB
dc:subject: Cranium
Mandible
Male
dc:description: Cranium (a) retains some teeth, though there is molar and incisor alveolar resorption. The cranial cavity is exposed at the right superior orbital surface. P3s each have two roots. Mandible (b) retains most teeth, though there is some alveolar resorption.
